Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pop the @sweet potato{200%g}(diced) onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) and cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges. Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a sieve.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Transfer the charred sweetcorn to a small #bowl{}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a sieve.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @chipotle paste{20%g}, @tomato passata{1%400g jar}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Season with salt and pepper.

Lightly crush half of the beans in the pan using a #potato masher{}, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sweet potato has roasted, stir it through the beans with a squeeze of lime juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} into the corn, then mix in the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the salsa.

Squeeze some lime juice into the salsa and gently mix through. Season with salt and pepper if needed.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and share between your bowls.

Spoon over the chipotle sweet potato and chorizo black beans.

Top with the charred corn and coriander salsa. Finish with any remaining lime wedges.

Enjoy!